## Installation

### Download from the App Store (iPhone and iPad)

1. Open the App Store on your iPhone or iPad.
2. Search for "Tranlate Documents - Offline" in the search bar.
3. Tap on the app icon in the search results.
4. On the app page, tap the "Get" or "Download" button.
5. Authenticate with your Apple ID, if prompted.
6. Wait for the app to download and install on your device.
7. Once installed, the app icon will appear on your home screen.

## Features

Tranlate Documents - Offline offers a feature to translate your Word Document to Text/PDF in 59 languages in a second without depending on the internet. Explore the following capabilities:

### Translator

Browse your Word Document with docx format from your Files. Select your Source to Target language to Translate. If the language Pack is not availble, it will ask to download to translate and it is one time process. You will always have option to uninstall or install Language pack from the settings page. Once you select the language, click Translator Button to translate and move to Text Editor Page with your Translated content from the word file. It is fast and accurate and works offline. 

### Manager

You can always edit and save the Translated file as a PDF or use Copy option to copy and paste whereever you want. You can store, view, delete, Print and share your PDF files from the Manager Page. 

###  settings

Using settings, you can download or uninstall Language Packs. For translation, you need to download Language packs offline and it is one time process. You always have an option to uninstall when it is not required.

